[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " During the time of the judges"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " there was a famine in the land of Judah."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So a man from Bethlehem"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in Judah went to live as a resident foreigner"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in the region of Moab, along with his wife and two sons."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (Now the man’s name was Elimelech,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his wife was Naomi,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and his two sons were Mahlon and Kilion."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They were of the clan of Ephrath"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " from Bethlehem in Judah.) They entered the region of Moab and settled there."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Sometime later"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Naomi’s husband Elimelech died, so she and her two sons were left alone. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So her sons"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " married"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Moabite women. (One was named Orpah and the other Ruth.)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And they continued to live there about ten years. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Naomi’s two sons, Mahlon and Kilion, also died."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So the woman was left all alone – bereaved of her two children"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " as well as her husband! "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So she decided to return home from the region of Moab, accompanied by her daughters-in-law,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " because while she was living in Moab"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " she had heard that the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " had shown concern"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for his people, reversing the famine by providing abundant crops."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now as she and her two daughters-in-law began to leave the place where she had been living to return to the land of Judah,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Naomi said to her two daughters-in-law, “Listen to me! Each of you should return to your mother’s home!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "May the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " show"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " you"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "the same kind of devotion that you have shown to your deceased husbands"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and to me!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " May the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " enable each of you to find"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " security"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in the home of a new husband!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then she kissed them goodbye and they wept loudly."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But they said to her, “No!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " We will"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " return with you to your people.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But Naomi replied, “Go back home, my daughters! There is no reason for you to return to Judah with me!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I am no longer capable of giving birth to sons who might become your husbands!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Go back home, my daughters! For I am too old to get married again."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Even if I thought that there was hope that I could get married tonight and conceive sons,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " surely you would not want to wait until they were old enough to marry!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Surely you would not remain unmarried all that time!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " No,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " my daughters, you must not return with me."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "For my intense suffering"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is too much for you to bear."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is afflicting me!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Again they wept loudly."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Orpah kissed her mother-in-law goodbye,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " but Ruth"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " clung tightly to her."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Naomi"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said, “Look, your sister-in-law is returning to her people and to her god."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Follow your sister-in-law back home!” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But Ruth replied, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“Stop urging me to abandon you!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "For wherever you go, I will go."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Wherever you live, I will live."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Your people will become my people,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "and your God will become my God."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Wherever you die, I will die – and there I will be buried."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "May the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " punish me severely if I do not keep my promise!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Only death will be able to separate me from you!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When Naomi"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " realized that Ruth"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " was determined to go with her, she stopped trying to dissuade her."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So the two of them"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " journeyed together until they arrived in Bethlehem."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "When they entered"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Bethlehem,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the whole village was excited about their arrival."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The women of the village said,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Can this be Naomi?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But she replied"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to them,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Don’t call me ‘Naomi’!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Call me ‘Mara’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " because the Sovereign One"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has treated me very harshly."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I left here full,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " but the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has caused me to return empty-handed."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Why do you call me ‘Naomi,’ seeing that"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has opposed me,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and the Sovereign One"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has caused me to suffer?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Naomi returned, accompanied by her Moabite daughter-in-law Ruth, who came back with her from the region of Moab."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (Now they"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " arrived in Bethlehem at the beginning of the barley harvest.)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]